description:
&lt;p&gt;Due to our existing senior audiologist is retiring we are looking for a Band 6 Audiologist to join our expanding and ambitious Audiology service. We are an enthusiastic, dedicated and friendly team and welcome your application. This post is cross site and the successful candidate will be expected to work and travel to all clinical sites across Harrow, Brent and Ealing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The post holder will be responsible for: &lt;br /&gt;Assessment and hearing management of adults with routine and complex needs including learning disabilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be involved in the training and mentoring of BSs and MSc students as we are a dedicated teaching department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be communicating with a range of people including professional, administrative staff and patients with communication difficulties.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be leading the trust in achieving the IQIPS accreditation. &lt;br /&gt;You should hold the appropriate qualifications and be registered with RCCP/HCPC.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is opportunity for CPD and this is strongly encouraged.&lt;br /&gt;We are committed to delivering the best possible care, putting patients at the HEART of everything we do.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In return we expect a dedicated, competent specialist senior audiologist, able to react and adapt to the ever changing needs of the department&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name:Denise McConnell&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Lead Adult Audiologist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: denisemcconnell@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 020 8869 2908&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Rosbin Syed, Head of Audiology via email : &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;rosbin.syed@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
